results.notes:
Collected near the Left Sawmill Loop Trail. Growing abundantly on dead Campsis radicans vines on and above the ground in a swampy area along a stream. Associated with a white rot. Caps purple when young (closest to weak red 5R 5/2 in Munsell but more vibrant purple) becoming pink (7.5YR 8/3). in age; glabrous; dry; up to 25.6 mm wide and 5.2 mm tall. Gills white (pale orange yellow 10YR 9.5/2 to 10YR 9/2); intervenose; adnate. Stems similar in color to caps but paler; reddish or orange dots present on some stem bases; eccentric; tapering toward the base; up to 5.2 mm long and 2.2 mm wide. Cap and stem context white. Not bioluminescent. Not fluorescent under a blacklight flashlight. Odor and taste not distinctive. Pileipellis a cutis of hyaline hyphae. Lamellar trama inamyloid. Clamps present in the lamellar trama. Pleurocystidia absent. Cheilocystidia abundnant; hyaline; apically branched. Basidia msotly 4-sterigmate with at least 1 2-sterigmate basidium present. Spores inamyloid, hylaine, smooth, and thin-walled. Spore print white. Spore measurements: (7.7) 8.6 – 10.6 (11) × (5.3) 5.4 – 6.4 (7.5) µm; Q = (1.3) 1.5 – 1.8 (1.9); N = 18; Me = 9.6 × 6 µm; Qe = 1.6

results.notes:
Growing in duff under a dead Picea engelmanii root in a seep area near P. engelmanii and Abies concolor. Caps dry; glabrous; up to 6.6 mm wide and 5.9 mm tall. Gills adnexed. Stems finely white-pruinose apically and smooth below; dry; with strigose bases; up to 17.3 mm long and 0.7 mm wide. Not fluorescing under a 365 nm blacklight. Not bioluminescent. Odor not distinctive. Lamellar trama inamyloid. Lactifers present in the lamellar trama. Pleurocystidia similar to cheilocystidia. Cheilocystidia hyaline, smooth, and fusoid-ventricose. Basidia 2-sterigmate and 4-sterigmate. Spores inamyloid, hyaline, smooth, and thin-walled. Spore measurements: (6.4) 6.5 – 8.4 (8.9) × (3.3) 3.7 – 5 (5.5) µm; Q = (1.4) 1.5 – 2; N = 20; Me = 7.3 × 4.3 µm; Qe = 1.7
